chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if your severe communication disorder affects your ability to drive safely.
chunks.plain_content:
Severe communication disorders and driving 
You must tell DVLA if your severe communication disorder affects your ability to drive safely.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Severe communication disorders and driving 
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you do not tell DVLA about a condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

chunks.html_content:
Ask your doctor if you’re not sure if your severe communication disorder will affect your driving.

Fill in form A1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
